Spec: SpecDD Docs Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in writing or updating user, developer, release, onboarding, or operational documentation from SpecDD specs.

Owns:
  ./specdd-docs/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-docs/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Identify the audience and documentation file authority before editing.
  Explain specified behavior without expanding the contract.
  Treat specs as source-adjacent contracts and documentation as explanatory material.
  Keep documentation aligned with changed specs, tasks, examples, and tests.
  Preserve operational constraints when user-facing behavior depends on them.
  Keep prose concise and concrete.
  Report specs used, docs changed, and behavior that remains underspecified.

Must not:
  Add promises, APIs, guarantees, or workflows unsupported by specs or implementation.
  Silently invent rules when documentation reveals a spec gap.
  Let documentation redefine source contracts or expand public behavior.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
